{"abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", the position between two cached points is interpolated cubically, and linearly otherwise."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"cubicInterp"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The points along the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Curve2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Path2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" are precomputed before use, for faster calculations. The point at the requested offset is then calculated interpolating between two adjacent cached points. This may present a problem if the curve makes sharp turns, as the cached points may not follow the curve closely enough.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two answers to this problem: either increase the number of cached points and increase memory consumption, or make a cubic interpolation between two points at the cost of (slightly) slower calculations."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/pathfollow2d\/cubicinterp"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot12PathFollow2DC11cubicInterpSbvp","roleHeading"